   "id": "fdbd994a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# PubMed Corpus — EDA\n",
    "\n",
    "Before running NER on the corpus, sanity-check what's in it:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. How many abstracts did we actually get? (Some PubMed records are\n",
    "   indexed without abstracts — these are dropped during parsing.)\n",
    "2. What's the temporal distribution? A query like \"kinase inhibitor\n",
    "   cancer\" should be heavily weighted toward the last 15-20 years.\n",
    "3. Which journals dominate? Useful for context when reading findings.\n",
    "4. Abstract length distribution — important for deciding whether to\n",
    "   process abstracts whole or split into sentences for NER.\n",
    "5. MeSH term frequency — gives a free preview of what entity types we\n",
    "   should expect (and serves as a non-trivial sanity check on whether\n",
    "   the corpus is coherent).\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "62769995",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Setup"
   ]
  },
