   "source": [
    "## 5. MeSH term frequency\n",
    "\n",
    "MeSH terms are human-curated. They're a useful preview of what entities\n",
    "we should expect from automatic NER — if 'Antineoplastic Agents' is\n",
    "the top MeSH term, we should expect a lot of drug entities; if 'EGFR'\n",
    "or 'BCR-ABL' show up high, we should see those genes/proteins."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "3dac3f92",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Distinct MeSH descriptors: 1,566\n",
      "Total MeSH annotations: 12,487\n",
      "Median MeSH per record (with annotations): 14\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "mesh_counter = Counter()\n",
    "for terms in df[\"mesh_terms\"]:\n",
    "    mesh_counter.update(terms)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Distinct MeSH descriptors: {len(mesh_counter):,}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Total MeSH annotations: {sum(mesh_counter.values()):,}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Median MeSH per record (with annotations): \"\n",
    "      f\"{df.loc[df['n_mesh'] > 0, 'n_mesh'].median():.0f}\")\n"
   ]
  },
